<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06082209 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06082209 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Commonwealth Edison Co. is shutting down both nuclear reactors at its Zion,Ill., generating station to investigate a safety system failure that shut offone of the reactors, a company spokesman said today. The utility shut downUnit 2 on Thursday after a transformer supplying power to its safety systemsfailed, spokesman Gary Wald said. Cold shutdown is a low level of operation.Wald said both reactors are out of service and will remain idle whileofficials try to find out what went wrong.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SAFETY SYSTEM FAILURE CLOSES NUCLEAR REACTORS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  National News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910322  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  88  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday March 22, 199100082209,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>